issues.description: I was just waiting for the B8 bus and as it pulled up, two large dump trucks sped around the bus in the opposite lane, into oncoming traffic on a two lane residential street, in the middle of an intersection. The trucks were going well above the 15 MPH speed limit and it looked like this wasn't the first time they've tried this trick to get around the bus, putting pedestrians and children (this location is right next to a public park, school, and home for the elderly), and other drivers in danger. Franklin St NE between Vista and Rhode Island Ave is abused by this kind of traffic daily. This is a residential street and these trucks should stay on Rhode Island ave. There is no need for them to cut through and pull moves like this that put residents in danger. There have been at least two accidents on Franklin Street between 18th and Rhode Island Ave in the last week. One resulted in a car that completely flipped over at the intersection of 17th and Franklin. With a 15mph speed limit on a residential street, this doesn't seem like the kind of thing that would happen here. The increased number of accidents in this section of road is evidence that the speed limit is not being observed and that oversized trucks are taking advantage of what could be a quiet neighborhood street. Please take action to insure the safety of our neighborhood!
